{
  "info": {
    "_postman_id": "ems-collection-2026-05-19",
    "name": "EMS API — Complete Collection",
    "description": "Complete Postman collection for the Employee Management System backend.\n\n## How to use\n\n1. Run the **Login** request for the role you want to test (Super Admin / HR Admin / Manager / Employee). The script auto-saves the token to a collection variable.\n2. Every other request uses `{{accessToken}}` automatically.\n3. To switch role: run a different Login request — the new token replaces the old one.\n\nNo other configuration required. Base URL is preset to production Render.",
    "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json"
  },
  "variable": [
    { "key": "baseUrl", "value": "https://employee-management-system-2b9q.onrender.com/api/v1", "type": "string" },
    { "key": "accessToken", "value": "", "type": "string" },
    { "key": "currentRole", "value": "", "type": "string" }
  ],
  "auth": {
    "type": "bearer",
    "bearer": [{ "key": "token", "value": "{{accessToken}}", "type": "string" }]
  },
  "item": [
    {
      "name": "1. LOGIN — pick a role",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Login as SUPER_ADMIN (superadmin@acme.test)",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "const d = pm.response.json();",
                  "pm.test('Login OK', () => pm.expect(d.success).to.equal(true));",
                  "pm.collectionVariables.set('accessToken', d.data.accessToken);",
                  "pm.collectionVariables.set('currentRole', d.data.user.memberType);",
                  "console.log('Logged in as', d.data.user.memberType, '—', d.data.user.email);"
                ]
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "auth": { "type": "noauth" },
            "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
            "body": { "mode": "raw", "raw": "{\n  \"email\": \"superadmin@acme.test\",\n  \"password\": \"Password123!\"\n}" },
            "url": { "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/auth/login", "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"], "path": ["auth", "login"] }
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Login as HR_ADMIN (hr@acme.test)",
